<task id="021" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Migrate ConversationPane to shared PaneHeader (FR-02)</title>
    <phase>Phase B — Assistant pane</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>010</dependencies>
    <blocks>022</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, fluent-ui, refactoring</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies a load-bearing .tsx file (ConversationPane) shared across the Assistant pane; replaces tab UI with consumption of new shared PaneHeader (ADR-012 load-bearing). FR-mapping with dark-mode + auth invariants requires FULL protocol.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Replace the existing `Chat | History` tab buttons inside `ConversationPane.tsx` with the
    shared `<PaneHeader title="Assistant" icon={ChatRegular}>` primitive from
    `@spaarke/ui-components` (Phase A task 010). The pane header's right-slot is reserved
    for the History overlay trigger button — wired in task 022. This task does NOT build
    the overlay; it only swaps the header and removes the tab-related state/handlers.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React 19 + Fluent v9 frontend developer experienced refactoring three-pane shell
    surfaces, comfortable removing local UI state cleanly without breaking the
    PaneEventBus subscriber graph.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `ConversationPane.tsx` no longer renders any `Chat | History` tab buttons. At the top of
    the pane, `<PaneHeader title="Assistant" icon={ChatRegular}>` is rendered with its icon
    in `tokens.colorBrandForeground1`. The `rightSlot` prop is reserved for the History
    button (added in task 022 — leave a clearly labelled comment placeholder). All tab-state
    related local React state, handlers, and unused imports are removed.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-02 replaces a custom two-tab control (Chat / History) with the unified `<PaneHeader>`
      primitive established in Phase A (task 010). The History tab itself becomes a side-overlay
      (OC-01, Claude-Code style) wired in task 022. This sequencing keeps the PaneHeader
      adoption simple here; task 022 then plugs in the HistoryRegular button + overlay into
      the rightSlot. Visual style must match ContextPaneController's existing header (canonical
      reference per plan §2 Discovered Resources).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/ConversationPane.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">PaneHeader is consumed from `@spaarke/ui-components` — do NOT duplicate the component locally. Import via the package path, not a relative file path.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Icon color must use `tokens.colorBrandForeground1`. No hex literals, no `rgba(...)` literals, no Fluent v8.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 only. No React 16 fallbacks. Do not add `useEffect` dependency array workarounds for removed state.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-025">ChatRegular icon comes from `@fluentui/react-icons` (Fluent v9). No new SVG web resources.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No `accessToken` props or state introduced. Any BFF calls in the pane continue to use `authenticatedFetch`. Do not snapshot tokens.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">PaneHeader visual style MUST match ContextPaneController's existing header (canonical reference); icon color = brand foreground 1; "Assistant" title uses Fluent v9 typography.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">This task touches ONLY `ConversationPane.tsx`. Task 022 separately edits the same file to wire rightSlot — coordinate the rightSlot placeholder so 022 lands cleanly.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-025-icon-library-and-deployment.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/spec.md</file>
